cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

This paper deals with improving the resolution of depth maps using deep learning methods and measuring the quality of the resulting 3D shapes. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of a trained CNN and deep prior, indicating that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with virtual reality applications, suggesting that it may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
